01:19.360 --> 01:21.237
THATCH ER: Mr Reid?

01:21.360 --> 01:23.271
Sir?

01:24.280 --> 01:26.112
Mr Reid?

01:27.560 --> 01:29.995
How is it you were taken?

01:31.920 --> 01:34.992
They say it was as though
you surrendered.

01:36.720 --> 01:38.119
Why?

01:39.160 --> 01:41.595
Sir, to what end? Hm?

01:42.640 --> 01:46.634
Did you and the Captain find Robin's
killed mother and uncle?

01:46.760 --> 01:48.910
(THATCHER SIGHS)

01:49.040 --> 01:52.317
On what rash instinct has he
and Miss Susan now blasted their way

01:52.440 --> 01:54.636
in and out of Mr Dove's home?

01:56.240 --> 01:58.151
Please?

02:01.320 --> 02:03.357
Please, Mr Reid.

02:06.160 --> 02:08.800
What must we do next?

02:13.800 --> 02:15.711
Mr Reid?

02:18.760 --> 02:20.398
Mr Reid?

03:00.000 --> 03:02.389
MAN: You can see
they came through this way.

03:02.520 --> 03:05.751
This is your case, Inspector Drummond.

03:05.880 --> 03:09.350
This may be Hackney, but this is a crime
birthed in Whitechapel.

03:09.480 --> 03:12.279
Its felons will no doubt be hid there
until their escape may be made

03:12.400 --> 03:14.630
and you, sir,
and your men at H Division,

03:14.760 --> 03:16.592
you shall hunt and trap them
in Whitechapel.

03:16.720 --> 03:19.189
- Am I clear?
- Yes, Mr Dove.

03:19.320 --> 03:21.709
Now that they've got the boy,
they must make their escape

03:21.840 --> 03:24.195
and must show themselves in so doing.

03:24.320 --> 03:26.470
Therefore, will you allow me more men
requisitioned from the] and the K?

03:26.600 --> 03:28.477
See the docksides locked down,
all the train stations likewise.

03:28.600 --> 03:30.716
She was mother to me
when I had need of one.

03:30.840 --> 03:32.558
(CLOCK TICKS)

03:32.680 --> 03:34.830
And they have stole my son.

03:36.080 --> 03:39.038
So, yes, Inspector, you shall
have all the men you require.

03:39.160 --> 03:41.276
- Only make the instruction.
- Yes, sir.

03:41.400 --> 03:42.310
And Mr Reid?

03:42.440 --> 03:44.670
Now that Mr Shine's last actions
have delivered him into your custody,

03:44.800 --> 03:47.758
- does he speak?
- He does not.

03:47.880 --> 03:50.918
And never mind what Mr Shine did to him.
It's...

03:51.040 --> 03:54.476
it's as if the marrow has been
sucked from his bones.

03:54.600 --> 03:57.513
The betrayal he has suffered.

03:57.640 --> 04:00.917
The perception of it, at least.
It is perhaps understandable.

04:01.960 --> 04:03.758
You have cleared the Leman Street cells
for his safety there?

04:03.880 --> 04:04.790
I have.

04:04.920 --> 04:07.116
Then perhaps I might interview him?

04:07.240 --> 04:09.390
I should be grateful, sir.

04:09.520 --> 04:12.638
Then let us to Leman Street.
After you, Inspector.

04:14.880 --> 04:19.397
MAN: Send for a photographer.
Do not let the mortuary men touch her.

04:53.600 --> 04:55.557
Thank you, Matthew.

04:56.600 --> 04:58.637
Thank you.

05:02.480 --> 05:04.357
I never knew...

05:04.480 --> 05:08.314
I never knew what it would be to see
the two of you together...

05:10.440 --> 05:12.909
...and to know myself changed.

05:15.240 --> 05:17.356
<i>And, Connor,</i>

05:17.480 --> 05:19.835
you watch your father,

05:19.960 --> 05:24.636
but, despite all, there is much
to take example from.

05:25.680 --> 05:27.398
His courage.

05:27.520 --> 05:30.239
His courage and his love.

05:31.440 --> 05:34.637
There are fences yet to be leapt.

05:35.960 --> 05:38.520
But we're going home, son,

05:38.640 --> 05:40.597
to America.

05:40.720 --> 05:42.597
And there, there are deep valleys

05:42.720 --> 05:46.509
and there are rivers that are fresh with
spring thaw.

05:49.840 --> 05:52.275
I have the carriage ready.

05:52.400 --> 05:54.710
My driver will take you
as far as the Old North Road

05:54.840 --> 05:56.877
and then make his own way home.

05:57.000 --> 05:59.594
Now, Connor, this is Miss Mimi,

05:59.720 --> 06:01.950
our true friend.

06:02.080 --> 06:03.798
Well, how else am I to be rid of you?

06:03.920 --> 06:05.877
The docks will be watched.

06:06.000 --> 06:08.992
The boat trains for the northern
and southern ports likewise.

06:09.120 --> 06:12.511
No, you'd only be apprehended,
escape once again, return here,

06:12.640 --> 06:15.029
and I should never be able to open
this playhouse to the paying public.

06:15.160 --> 06:17.515
All right. Best we're about it, then.

06:19.720 --> 06:20.710
Aha.

06:21.800 --> 06:26.237
You do not wish to hear news
of the wider world of Whitechapel?

06:26.360 --> 06:29.512
- We do not.
- And what news is that, Miss Mimi?

06:29.640 --> 06:32.439
Jedediah Shine is dead.

06:37.520 --> 06:40.876
Well, that's cause
for celebration, then.

06:41.000 --> 06:41.910
How so?

06:42.040 --> 06:44.475
Er...it is not said in detail...

06:47.000 --> 06:50.277
...only that the capture of Mr Reid was
his last living act.

06:53.040 --> 06:56.192
It appears Mr Reid's daughter
was turned to his betrayal.

06:57.960 --> 07:00.474
JACKSON: Hey, he knew the risk.
I warned him.

07:00.600 --> 07:04.559
But he decided to go his own way,
just as now we're gonna go ours.

07:04.680 --> 07:09.151
Caitlin, you bring the boy. I'm gonna take
the bags out to the carriage.

07:12.040 --> 07:13.599
Caitlin, I said bring the boy.

07:13.720 --> 07:17.111
Matthew, I have to.
I made the promise.

07:17.240 --> 07:20.278
That betrayal, that sundering,
they are down to me.

07:20.400 --> 07:22.516
God damn it, Caitlin.

07:22.640 --> 07:23.550
No.

07:23.680 --> 07:26.911
Or does he not merit intervention?
Does she not deserve the truth?

07:27.040 --> 07:28.872
And what about us,
for Christ's sakes?

07:29.000 --> 07:31.799
We have him, we have Connor,

07:31.920 --> 07:33.672
and now you're going to go
saunter over

07:33.800 --> 07:36.633
and present yourself to the home address
of Inspector Samuel Drummond?

07:36.760 --> 07:39.559
I do not suggest such a thing.

07:39.680 --> 07:41.796
Then what?

07:41.920 --> 07:44.230
(DOOR RATTLES AND CREAKS)

07:50.760 --> 07:52.114
(DOG BARKS OUTSIDE)

07:52.240 --> 07:54.754
DOVE: Will you leave us a moment,
Inspector Drummond?

07:54.880 --> 07:57.394
Yes, sir.

08:00.880 --> 08:03.190
(DOG BARKS OUTSIDE)

08:03.320 --> 08:06.676
(DOOR SHUTS)

08:06.800 --> 08:09.030
All of London is a-clamour, sir.

08:10.120 --> 08:12.714
The capital's press
is therefore to be gathered

08:12.840 --> 08:15.275
at Scotland Yard tomorrow morning...

08:16.320 --> 08:20.473
...where I shall explain to them the ugly
whys and wherefores of how it is

08:20.600 --> 08:25.117
the leading police of Whitechapel are
either murdered or murdering.

08:29.720 --> 08:31.393
I'm sure you...

08:31.520 --> 08:34.717
understand, therefore...

08:37.000 --> 08:38.798
...a service you would render,

08:38.919 --> 08:41.753
should you give full account of...

08:43.960 --> 08:45.792
...all you know.

08:51.040 --> 08:52.838
Your friends have killed once more.

08:52.960 --> 08:55.520
More blood,

08:55.640 --> 08:58.234
the spattering of which
lands on your shirt cuffs, Mr Reid,

08:58.360 --> 09:01.796
for you know where they might be found
and will not say.

09:03.440 --> 09:05.397
Will you now tell me?

09:15.160 --> 09:18.073
And be aware I do not offer you terms.

09:18.200 --> 09:19.110
You are wiser than to think

09:19.240 --> 09:24.155
your many articles of disgrace might be
shrived for one act of confession.

09:24.280 --> 09:28.069
No, you speak, because you understand
that this mayhem must come to an end.

09:28.200 --> 09:32.159
You do it because
you believe in a resolution.

09:32.280 --> 09:34.510
(WHISPERS) A last good act for
Edmund Reid.

09:36.280 --> 09:39.238
It will not erase the stain
of your works, sir.

09:39.360 --> 09:40.634
But it will return a measure of order

09:40.760 --> 09:43.752
to the community
you have purported to serve...

09:47.400 --> 09:49.391
...and some peace

09:49.520 --> 09:52.114
to the shattered soul
of your daughter.

09:56.440 --> 09:59.558
I could hear Bennet Drake
as he died.

10:00.960 --> 10:04.078
I heard what it was
he said to your brother,

10:04.200 --> 10:07.397
before your brother took his throat out.

10:09.200 --> 10:11.271
Bennet said

10:11.400 --> 10:14.199
that to see him was
only looking in a mirror...

10:15.600 --> 10:17.796
...and now you and I here,

10:17.920 --> 10:19.274
facing reflections of our own.

10:21.960 --> 10:24.429
I know you sincere, Mr Dove...

10:27.320 --> 10:31.917
...sincere in your hope that the world be
righted and renewed...

10:32.920 --> 10:35.878
...the pitiless murk of the past

10:36.000 --> 10:38.116
be obliterated and forgot.

10:39.320 --> 10:42.073
This journey here,

10:42.200 --> 10:44.032
<i>GUYS,</i>

10:44.160 --> 10:47.039
began with a man named
Isaac Bloom.

10:48.200 --> 10:49.429
You recall the name?

10:52.400 --> 10:53.435
Isaac was a mathematician.

10:53.560 --> 10:57.190
He believed that numbers betrayed
the true nature of our universe

10:57.320 --> 10:59.231
and that, accordingly,
it was empirically proved

10:59.360 --> 11:03.558
that the entropy of the universe extended
to a maximum,

11:03.680 --> 11:08.117
that everything moved
irretrievably from order

11:08.240 --> 11:09.719
into chaos.

11:12.360 --> 11:14.078
You do not believe that, do you?

11:14.200 --> 11:15.998
I cannot.

11:16.120 --> 11:20.637
REID: I said the same, because what hope
for Whitechapel if he were right?

11:23.480 --> 11:25.551
You wish for a confession
of truth from me?

11:26.600 --> 11:27.510
I do.

11:27.640 --> 11:29.916
Well, this is it.

11:30.040 --> 11:32.429
Isaac Bloom was correct
in all that he said.

11:34.560 --> 11:36.517
You forget your hopes, sir,

11:36.640 --> 11:38.153
because this Whitechapel
is coming for you.

11:41.280 --> 11:43.794
The one last good act, you say?

11:46.720 --> 11:48.757
Then I choose the simplest.

11:49.760 --> 11:51.876
I will not betray my friends.

12:17.360 --> 12:21.354
He will not speak.
But we must proceed, regardless.

12:21.480 --> 12:24.438
The man he is, his position
in your own private life,

12:24.560 --> 12:26.710
it is no easy thing, I know.

12:27.760 --> 12:29.671
But you see him charged, Inspector.

12:29.800 --> 12:31.837
I shall, Mr Dove.

12:34.360 --> 12:38.194
My, but you are upright,
the pair of you.

12:38.320 --> 12:40.675
Careful, Frank.

12:40.800 --> 12:43.519
What is it scares you, Drum?

12:43.640 --> 12:46.314
That just as the sanctified
Miss Mathilda Reid has done,

12:46.440 --> 12:50.832
we too might find cause to wallop you
in full view of the world?

12:50.960 --> 12:53.759
Are you about your work,
Desk Sergeant?

12:53.880 --> 12:56.269
Have you wired the] and K
about them extra boots?

12:56.400 --> 12:58.630
Do they even now read
their instructions

12:58.760 --> 13:00.990
as to how each and every means of
departure from this town

13:01.120 --> 13:03.350
is to be barricaded?

13:04.440 --> 13:06.078
No? Then see it done!

13:06.200 --> 13:09.511
And when you have, you may come
and witness Mr Reid's charge sheet.

13:09.640 --> 13:11.631
Hear his of fences for yourself.

13:50.600 --> 13:52.876
Please confirm your name.

13:53.000 --> 13:53.990
Edmund john James Reid.

13:54.120 --> 13:57.397
- Address?
- 14 Fairclough Street, Whitechapel.

13:57.520 --> 13:58.794
Occupation?

14:00.720 --> 14:02.438
Police officer. Drummond?

14:02.560 --> 14:06.713
What I asked of you earlier,
you told Mathilda?

14:08.320 --> 14:09.993
That I understand, that I understood?

14:11.400 --> 14:13.038
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

14:13.160 --> 14:15.390
Please, will you tell her?

14:17.760 --> 14:19.080
Please say that you'll tell her.

14:19.200 --> 14:23.319
(CLEARS THROAT) Charge sheet against
Reid, Edmund john James. Witness.

14:23.440 --> 14:25.317
Sergeant Francis Thatcher.

14:25.440 --> 14:28.478
Her Majesty's Metropolitan Police
do charge you with the following crimes.

14:28.600 --> 14:32.230
The unlawful murder with
malice aforethought of Theodore Swift.

14:32.360 --> 14:33.270
The unlawful murder

14:33.400 --> 14:34.276
- of Horace Buckley.
- Drum.

14:34.400 --> 14:36.516
Aiding and abetting in the unlawful murder
of Frank Goodnight.

14:36.640 --> 14:38.313
Resisting arrest.

14:38.440 --> 14:40.033
- Drummond.
- Conspiracy to defeat justice.

14:40.160 --> 14:41.355
- Please, Mathilda must know.
- Being an accessory after the fact...

14:41.480 --> 14:43.391
- Please, Mathilda must know.
-...to the felony of permitting...

14:43.520 --> 14:44.430
- She must not suffer...
-...Miss Susan Hart...

14:44.560 --> 14:45.630
-...any further distress.
-...and Captain Homer Jackson...

14:45.760 --> 14:46.750
to regain their liberty,

14:46.880 --> 14:48.951
whilst having the prisoners
in your lawful custody.

14:49.080 --> 14:50.195
- It is only a message.
- You will sign here, Mr Reid.

14:50.320 --> 14:51.674
Why will you not undertake to give it?

14:51.800 --> 14:52.710
And then you, Frank.

14:52.840 --> 14:54.433
He cannot undertake to do that, Mr Reid,

14:54.560 --> 14:57.552
because Miss Mathilda put him out
on the streets and won't speak to him.

15:01.960 --> 15:04.600
Is this true, Drummond?

15:04.720 --> 15:07.075
- Please, sir, sign...
- REID: Tell me.

15:11.720 --> 15:15.679
- Sergeant Thatcher, sign.
- Samuel Drummond?

15:16.840 --> 15:20.629
Was it you who lit the candle
in Mathilda's window?

15:38.480 --> 15:42.269
Sergeant Thatcher, earlier, you were
enquiring after the Sumner family.

15:42.400 --> 15:43.310
Yes, Mr Reid.

15:43.440 --> 15:46.637
Perhaps one and a half kilometres
upstream from the Limehouse Cut,

15:46.760 --> 15:49.718
there is a series of heavy meanders
through Bow Creek

15:49.840 --> 15:51.990
and on the eastern bank

15:52.120 --> 15:55.636
there is a copse of black poplars
at Goodluck Hope.

15:55.760 --> 15:59.594
Amongst, you will find a mound of earth
marked with a prow of driftwood

15:59.720 --> 16:04.590
and within that grave you will find
the murdered body of Robin Sumner.

16:10.360 --> 16:12.795
H Ow?

16:12.920 --> 16:14.672
Who?

16:14.800 --> 16:16.598
Who?

16:16.720 --> 16:19.030
Commissioner Dove, I believe.

16:27.280 --> 16:28.759
That man.

16:28.880 --> 16:33.033
And that Inspector Drum, up there
with his vanity and his ambition,

16:33.160 --> 16:35.913
he may as well have the little boy's blood
on his hands as well.

16:36.040 --> 16:38.350
Well, he shall hear what he's done.

16:38.480 --> 16:39.390
No. No, no.

16:39.520 --> 16:42.433
Samuel Drummond...Samuel Drummond is
innocent of all and must remain so.

16:42.560 --> 16:44.631
Sir? The candle. Miss Mathilda.
How can you defend him?

16:44.760 --> 16:46.751
It was done for the love of her.

16:49.240 --> 16:50.833
Whichever, Sergeant.

16:50.960 --> 16:53.554
It serves no purpose to ruin
his sense of the world.

16:53.680 --> 16:56.035
Not yet, at any rate.

16:56.160 --> 16:58.629
Then I ask you again, sir.

17:00.160 --> 17:02.117
What must we do now?

17:02.240 --> 17:05.198
Not we, Francis Thatcher.

17:06.359 --> 17:08.237
You.

17:09.280 --> 17:11.635
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS)

17:14.839 --> 17:16.797
(HAWKER SHOUTS)

17:21.520 --> 17:24.319
You are Miss Mathilda Reid?

17:24.440 --> 17:26.431
Yes. Who are you?

17:36.640 --> 17:39.200
This is my theatre, Miss Reid.

17:39.320 --> 17:43.359
It means a great deal to me so I do hope
that you can be trusted.

18:02.920 --> 18:04.877
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

18:07.600 --> 18:08.829
Hello, Mathilda.

18:13.000 --> 18:15.389
Why am I brought here?

18:15.520 --> 18:16.999
Because she asks.

18:17.120 --> 18:21.193
And she has a way
of getting what she asks for.

18:21.320 --> 18:24.836
You bank a great deal
on my discretion, Miss Susan.

18:24.960 --> 18:28.157
I hope you will consider it
a risk worth taking.

18:28.280 --> 18:30.920
Then what is it that I may do for you?

18:31.040 --> 18:33.236
Relieve me of a secret,

18:33.360 --> 18:35.636
I hope.

18:35.760 --> 18:36.989
How may I do that?

18:37.120 --> 18:39.316
Allow me to tell it to you...

18:40.320 --> 18:43.039
...for I've kept it long
and it is to me a poison.

18:43.160 --> 18:45.515
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

18:51.760 --> 18:53.797
Hello, Connor.

18:54.880 --> 18:58.271
My son knows a friend when he sees one.

19:02.680 --> 19:04.512
May I fetch you some tea,
Miss Reid?

19:05.640 --> 19:07.551
Thank you, Captain Jackson.

19:11.320 --> 19:13.357
LONG SUSAN: We heard
the news of your father.

19:13.480 --> 19:16.233
He was hid here with us until...

19:17.640 --> 19:18.835
Well, you called to him,

19:18.960 --> 19:21.554
and which father can resist
the call of his child?

19:21.680 --> 19:23.830
But I did not call to him,

19:23.960 --> 19:26.873
did not send him out to go
beneath Mr Shine's fists.

19:27.000 --> 19:28.035
I would not. I could not.

19:28.160 --> 19:30.834
LONG SUSAN: I believe it, Mathilda.
You love him.

19:32.600 --> 19:34.591
MATHILDA: I do.

19:37.160 --> 19:38.195
And yet...

19:38.320 --> 19:39.958
LONG SUSAN: The things he has done?

19:46.040 --> 19:47.838
May I tell you about my father?

19:55.920 --> 19:58.116
(LONG SUSAN TALKS)

20:08.440 --> 20:09.510
Are you feeling all right?

20:09.640 --> 20:11.711
Oh, um...

20:11.840 --> 20:13.194
a little flu.

20:13.320 --> 20:16.119
LONG SUSAN:...great ambition,

20:16.240 --> 20:19.278
what he suffered
and for all its horror...

20:21.640 --> 20:25.315
...I wished for Mr Reid to lock the grille
and leave my father there.

20:25.440 --> 20:27.670
Forgive me, Miss Susan.

20:27.800 --> 20:32.192
But your father's fate,
my own's involvement in that,

20:32.320 --> 20:35.551
it is not those actions
which brought me to despair.

20:35.680 --> 20:36.670
I know, Mathilda.

20:36.800 --> 20:39.030
But Mr Buckley...
what he did to Mr Buckley...

20:39.160 --> 20:43.472
Mathilda, this...this is
why I bring you here.

20:45.800 --> 20:47.677
Whenever,

20:47.800 --> 20:49.473
down the years,

20:49.600 --> 20:53.719
you bring to mind the picture
of what befell Mr Buckley in that cellar,

20:53.840 --> 20:58.960
you no more imagine Mr Reid
with that man's head between his fists...

21:00.320 --> 21:01.674
...but myself.

21:03.920 --> 21:06.070
Now, it would take you
another lifetime to understand

21:06.200 --> 21:10.239
what would have made me do...
do such a thing,

21:10.360 --> 21:12.192
but at the time I believed your father

21:12.320 --> 21:16.314
perhaps as vicious as your...your worst
dreams may suggest...

21:17.720 --> 21:19.791
...and...

21:19.920 --> 21:22.992
(SNIFFS)...to my shame,

21:23.120 --> 21:25.236
my life...

21:25.360 --> 21:27.351
my lifelong shame,

21:27.480 --> 21:30.279
I saw a way by which...

21:31.360 --> 21:32.998
...all that I had made for myself...

21:35.280 --> 21:38.830
...all that your father would set himself
upon taking from me,

21:38.960 --> 21:42.794
I saw a means to protect it
and that means was a lie.

21:43.880 --> 21:48.078
In the days after you were found,
taken into my care,

21:48.200 --> 21:50.760
your mind fevered, wandering,

21:50.880 --> 21:55.795
the damaged spirit child Mr Buckley had
made you believe that you were...

22:00.480 --> 22:04.155
...your father, Mr Reid,
came looking for you

22:04.280 --> 22:06.476
and I told him you were dead.

22:06.600 --> 22:09.069
(SOBS) And worse, Mathilda.

22:11.080 --> 22:14.630
For Mr Buckley's gentleness to you,

22:14.760 --> 22:17.513
I described a vision of horror
to your father,

22:17.640 --> 22:21.270
that you had been chained and starved
and...and violated

22:21.400 --> 22:23.118
all those years that
you'd been gone from him.

22:23.240 --> 22:25.197
So, yes, he took Horace Buckley's life.

22:25.320 --> 22:27.789
But with my hands, Mathilda.

22:29.520 --> 22:30.999
My hands.

22:32.960 --> 22:34.189
My hands.

22:34.320 --> 22:35.993
As...

22:37.000 --> 22:39.310
...as though he were my puppet.

22:44.440 --> 22:46.954
It's true, Miss Reid.

22:47.080 --> 22:49.230
All of it.

22:53.760 --> 22:58.197
And so you bring me here
now to tell me this,

22:58.320 --> 23:01.119
because you have your son,
are leaving,

23:01.240 --> 23:03.993
and wish to unburden yourself
before you do?

23:04.120 --> 23:09.115
Forgive me, but, as ever, I feel you serve
no-one's ends but your own.

23:10.320 --> 23:12.118
Think on it,

23:12.240 --> 23:16.120
as my father is dragged
pitilessly to his justice,

23:16.240 --> 23:18.072
while you escape yours.

23:19.960 --> 23:22.190
JACKSON: God damn it!

23:23.440 --> 23:25.477
You just couldn't leave well enough alone,
could you?

23:25.600 --> 23:28.718
Of all the women in the world to have
an attack of conscience.

23:28.840 --> 23:30.797
Jesus Christ.

23:32.720 --> 23:35.075
God damn it.

23:35.200 --> 23:37.760
I mean, what did he
ever do for me, huh?

23:37.880 --> 23:40.554
Hauled his flapping ass out of
more scrapes than I care to think of,

23:40.680 --> 23:41.795
and now...

23:41.920 --> 23:43.991
Now what, Captain?

23:48.520 --> 23:50.750
I have a goddamn plan...

23:50.880 --> 23:51.995
that's what.

24:04.320 --> 24:06.197
I see him, Sarge.

24:10.400 --> 24:13.438
Evening, boys.
You took your sweet time.

24:13.560 --> 24:16.074
Think it's gonna take six of you, do you?

24:16.200 --> 24:18.316
Well, perhaps it might...

24:19.360 --> 24:21.192
...if you were men

24:21.320 --> 24:23.277
and not cowards and eunuchs.

24:24.960 --> 24:27.190
Come on, darlings.

24:36.640 --> 24:38.711
Where's Sergeant Thatcher?

24:38.840 --> 24:41.036
- Don't know, sir.
- Well, somebody bloody find him!

24:41.160 --> 24:43.436
(RAISED VOICES)

24:43.560 --> 24:45.312
Stay there!

24:46.760 --> 24:49.479
Well, Drummond, the fairy queen himself.

25:08.680 --> 25:12.878
Whatever it is you have in mind,
do not take me for a fool.

25:14.840 --> 25:16.717
DRUMMOND: Has he been searched?

25:18.200 --> 25:19.190
Strip him.

25:21.080 --> 25:22.991
Do it!

25:41.080 --> 25:42.514
- Inspector, sir...
- What?

25:42.640 --> 25:43.550
You're called for.

25:43.680 --> 25:46.194
I'm occupied.
Take a note or send them away.

25:46.320 --> 25:48.231
RENSHAW: It is Miss Reid, sir.

25:48.360 --> 25:51.159
(DISTANT DOG BARKS)

25:56.760 --> 26:00.799
Lock Captain Jackson down.
Two men on the outer door also.

26:14.520 --> 26:16.193
What is it you do, Captain?

26:16.320 --> 26:20.917
Attack of conscience, Reid, and you can
save your gratitude for later.

26:21.040 --> 26:25.352
And why am I grateful that
you too are now incarcerated?

26:27.080 --> 26:27.990
Why do you think?

26:28.120 --> 26:31.397
Not that you deserve it, but we're gonna
break you out of here.

26:31.520 --> 26:33.591
We?

26:38.440 --> 26:40.954
Tilda?

26:45.600 --> 26:47.750
Tilda.

26:47.880 --> 26:50.440
Will you come upstairs so we may talk?

26:51.480 --> 26:54.393
In due course, perhaps.

26:54.520 --> 26:57.273
For now, I would see my father.

26:57.400 --> 26:59.118
Drum, you may take a moment

26:59.240 --> 27:00.799
to consider the consequences
of denying me this,

27:00.920 --> 27:02.957
but do not take any longer.

27:06.480 --> 27:08.278
(DOOR RATTLES AND CREAKS)

27:14.920 --> 27:17.514
Thank you, Drum. As I said, alone.

27:19.760 --> 27:22.070
I shall wait beyond.

27:22.200 --> 27:25.795
Hammer on the door
when you are done, Tilda.

27:28.000 --> 27:29.229
- Father.
- Darling girl.

27:29.360 --> 27:32.352
- Are you hurt? What that man did...
- Hush, Mathilda. I shall live.

27:32.480 --> 27:34.994
My candle.
It was not myself to have lit it.

27:35.120 --> 27:37.555
I know. I know, Mathilda.

27:37.680 --> 27:38.590
But how?

27:38.720 --> 27:41.758
Mr Drummond is not a man much able
to disguise his shame.

27:41.880 --> 27:43.200
- He told you?
- Not as such.

27:43.320 --> 27:45.231
But he bears it hard, my darling.

27:45.360 --> 27:47.431
Hey, my heart bleeds for him,
really, but, Miss Reid,

27:47.560 --> 27:50.951
do you think it's about time we got about
our chief purpose?

27:53.120 --> 27:54.838
No, no. No.

27:54.960 --> 27:57.600
No, I am not for the freeing, Mathilda.

27:57.720 --> 28:00.519
- Excuse me?
- No more running, no more, no more.

28:00.640 --> 28:02.677
But, Miss Susan,
she explained all to me.

28:02.800 --> 28:04.677
No, no. Not all.

28:04.800 --> 28:06.473
The man, Buckley, perhaps.

28:06.600 --> 28:10.480
Her father, Theodore Swift,
I can never regret that.

28:10.600 --> 28:16.118
But think on your Uncle Bennet
and all I brought him to.

28:17.880 --> 28:21.111
Mathilda, an accounting must be made.

28:21.240 --> 28:23.277
And now you're happy
to let me hang alongside you,

28:23.400 --> 28:26.358
when I bust my ass in here to free you?

28:26.480 --> 28:27.754
Yes.

28:27.880 --> 28:29.917
On that matter,
it is my own strategy, Captain,

28:30.040 --> 28:32.111
and I very much hope
it shan't come to that.

28:32.240 --> 28:33.878
And that strategy being what?

28:34.000 --> 28:37.072
Francis Thatcher is gone to exhume
the body of Robin Sumner.

28:41.200 --> 28:43.999
I thought you said
you left that boy to rest.

28:44.120 --> 28:46.953
He rests. Augustus Dove prevails.

28:48.000 --> 28:49.673
Now, he may rest in due course again,

28:49.800 --> 28:53.316
but it is that boy who will give his own
tragedy...

28:53.440 --> 28:55.750
His family is here, Bennet Drake's,
Isaac Bloom's.

28:55.880 --> 28:58.918
It is that boy who will hand
them their justice,

28:59.040 --> 29:00.474
even if I am handed mine alongside.

29:00.600 --> 29:04.878
And how is the boy to do that, Reid?
That boy cannot speak.

29:05.000 --> 29:08.470
The dead can always speak, Captain,
when you are there to aid them.

29:11.560 --> 29:14.154
- (BIRDS TWEET)
- (CARRIAGE APPROACH ES)

29:14.280 --> 29:17.033
(DOOR OPENS)

29:18.680 --> 29:21.911
My apologies, brother.
I have left you alone too long.

29:22.040 --> 29:23.314
I thought we might eat together.

29:47.360 --> 29:51.115
Last night, as we came under attack,
you broke down your door.

29:51.240 --> 29:52.150
I did.

29:52.280 --> 29:55.398
DOVE: You did this so you might assist
my people?

29:59.240 --> 30:00.719
I heard the pup calling.

30:00.840 --> 30:03.753
And yet you did not protect him?

30:05.120 --> 30:06.952
Well, the Captain, he...

30:07.080 --> 30:09.674
he had a pistol.

30:09.800 --> 30:11.632
- And besides...
- Besides what, brother?

30:15.560 --> 30:16.755
Miss Susan is his mother.

30:16.880 --> 30:19.315
She is a murderer, Nathaniel.

30:21.320 --> 30:23.391
So am I, Gustus.

30:33.640 --> 30:35.950
Do you recall the boy Robin Sumner?

30:37.280 --> 30:38.953
Of course.

30:39.080 --> 30:41.230
(DOGS BARK OUTSIDE)

30:41.360 --> 30:43.351
Miss Susan told me...

30:43.480 --> 30:46.438
he is, in fact, not safe,

30:46.560 --> 30:48.392
but he is dead.

30:51.200 --> 30:53.555
And she knows this how?

30:53.680 --> 30:56.320
NATHANIEL:
Captain found him in water...

30:57.680 --> 30:59.990
...at Goodluck Hope.

31:03.120 --> 31:06.636
How dead, did these
most valued witnesses say?

31:07.680 --> 31:10.069
Killed...

31:11.200 --> 31:13.794
...by you, they believe.

31:16.640 --> 31:19.519
And what do you believe, Nathaniel?

31:19.640 --> 31:22.917
You, who have known me your entire life.

31:24.640 --> 31:26.677
Do you truly believe
I could do that to a pup?

31:30.200 --> 31:32.430
A pup?

31:36.040 --> 31:37.030
No.

31:40.480 --> 31:43.120
Now, we are almost home.

31:43.240 --> 31:46.790
Edmund Reid lies in a cell
at Leman Street, his spirit broken.

31:46.920 --> 31:49.434
The woman Hart and her American must
now escape with their child

31:49.560 --> 31:52.712
and will surely be taken in so doing.

31:55.920 --> 31:58.434
It will be Christmas before we know it.

31:58.560 --> 32:02.713
We shall fill the house with
food and gifts and friends

32:02.840 --> 32:06.515
and give thanks
for the future ahead of us.

32:09.480 --> 32:10.470
Eat.

32:29.480 --> 32:31.994
(BIRDS TWEET)

32:32.120 --> 32:34.430
(GULLS CRY)

32:40.880 --> 32:42.314
Right.

32:51.040 --> 32:52.394
(SNIFFS)

33:21.280 --> 33:23.556
(BREATHES HARD)

33:36.480 --> 33:38.517
(BIRDS TWEET)

33:40.400 --> 33:42.471
(GATE SQUEAKS)

34:04.200 --> 34:07.113
- (RUNNING WATER)
- (CROWS CAW)

34:08.760 --> 34:11.195
(RUNNING WATER)

34:12.280 --> 34:14.271
(BREATHES HARD)

34:19.239 --> 34:21.914
(RUNNING WATER)

34:22.040 --> 34:24.110
I will fear no evil...

34:25.840 --> 34:27.717
...for thou art with me;

34:27.840 --> 34:31.913
thy rod and thy staff,
they comfort me.

34:33.199 --> 34:35.315
(SNIFFS)

34:47.239 --> 34:48.958
Oh.

34:49.080 --> 34:51.150
(BREATHES HARD)

34:58.560 --> 35:00.312
(GULPS)

35:01.360 --> 35:03.556
(SOBS)

35:06.120 --> 35:08.031
Oh, Robin.

35:09.560 --> 35:12.757
How did you know where
to find him, Sergeant?

35:16.840 --> 35:18.717
Mr Reid told me where.

35:18.840 --> 35:21.434
And what will you do with him now?

35:25.080 --> 35:26.912
Get him his retribution.

35:29.920 --> 35:33.276
DOVE: An admirable instinct, Mr Thatcher.

35:33.400 --> 35:34.754
A policeman's instinct.

35:34.880 --> 35:36.791
(GUNSHOT)

35:39.840 --> 35:42.195
(GRUNTS)

35:42.320 --> 35:45.836
You have saved me
a great deal of trouble.

35:45.960 --> 35:47.109
I should have been here
all night otherwise.

35:52.840 --> 35:54.911
(GRUNTS)

35:57.400 --> 35:59.152
(THATCH ER GRUNTS)

35:59.280 --> 36:01.078
(SOBS)

36:02.240 --> 36:04.231
(RUNNING WATER)

36:06.680 --> 36:08.671
(THATCH ER SOBS)

36:12.520 --> 36:15.239
(THATCH ER GRUNTS)

36:16.280 --> 36:17.953
- It is a faster current here...
- (GROANS)

36:18.080 --> 36:21.232
...and the course runs direct.

36:21.360 --> 36:23.476
Do you see?

36:23.600 --> 36:26.069
The pilot lights at Limehouse Cut.

36:26.200 --> 36:30.478
The Thames running on the spring tide
and beyond the ocean.

36:31.960 --> 36:34.713
As you sought to show Robin Sumner
his path in life,

36:34.840 --> 36:36.035
you will lead him on in death now.

36:36.160 --> 36:38.151
(GROANS)

36:43.320 --> 36:45.277
(RUNNING WATER)

36:49.760 --> 36:52.149
(BREATHES HARD)

37:23.080 --> 37:25.196
(WATER SPLASH ES)

37:28.840 --> 37:30.751
(BREATHES HARD)

37:32.160 --> 37:34.913
(BREATHES HARD)

37:59.000 --> 38:00.911
(SIGHS)

38:03.080 --> 38:04.957
(SIGHS)

38:07.000 --> 38:09.116
(JACKSON PACES)

38:14.040 --> 38:17.556
Whichever road Thatcher took, he's late.

38:17.680 --> 38:19.432
He is way, way late.

38:22.520 --> 38:24.511
(JACKSON SIGHS)

38:24.640 --> 38:28.520
Yeah, they're waiting for me, you know?
My wife, my boy.

38:28.640 --> 38:31.029
For you too, if you need a ride.

38:35.840 --> 38:39.913
We have the guns,
we have the dynamite, Reid.

38:40.040 --> 38:42.429
We might...just go.

38:45.160 --> 38:47.117
You might.

38:47.240 --> 38:49.311
You ought.

38:49.440 --> 38:51.431
Whatever has happened. Whatever is
coming, I cannot explain it.

38:51.560 --> 38:54.473
But I...I must be here to see it.

38:54.600 --> 38:57.114
But I am in earnest, Captain.

38:57.240 --> 38:59.959
You go. Go now.

39:02.280 --> 39:04.430
What?

39:04.560 --> 39:07.234
And let you martyr yourself all alone?

39:49.760 --> 39:51.671
(BIRDS TWEET OUTSIDE)

40:07.640 --> 40:09.074
Nathaniel!

40:09.200 --> 40:10.554
Nathaniel!

40:17.720 --> 40:19.757
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

40:21.400 --> 40:23.676
OFFICER: Mr Dove, sir,
your carriage is here.

40:23.800 --> 40:26.269
(CLICKS WATCH)

40:27.320 --> 40:29.118
(CLICKS WATCH)

40:59.000 --> 41:00.991
(LOW CHATTER)

41:06.960 --> 41:09.395
(CLOCK CHIMES)

41:11.640 --> 41:13.677
(CLOCK CHIMES)

41:16.360 --> 41:19.079
(CHATTER)

41:22.560 --> 41:25.120
(CHATTER INTENSIFIES)

41:28.040 --> 41:29.314
(CHATTER)

41:33.720 --> 41:35.358
(CHATTER)

41:35.480 --> 41:37.915
Order.

41:38.040 --> 41:40.634
(CHATTER)

41:40.760 --> 41:42.956
God damn you, silence!

41:43.080 --> 41:44.912
(CHATTER HALTS)

41:45.040 --> 41:47.793
So that the newspapermen of London may
be furnished with the truth,

41:47.920 --> 41:51.356
Assistant Commissioner Dove
will now elaborate.

41:51.480 --> 41:54.154
Thank you, Commissioner.

41:56.240 --> 41:59.119
It is with regret
I must announce the death

41:59.240 --> 42:02.198
of Inspector First Class jedediah Shine
of H Division, Whitechapel.

42:02.320 --> 42:04.118
(CHATTER)

42:04.240 --> 42:05.958
WOMAN: How do you respond to
rumours...

42:06.080 --> 42:08.356
(GAVEL BANGS)

42:08.480 --> 42:11.313
- Please.
- (CHATTER PAUSES)

42:11.440 --> 42:13.397
Mr Shine was as fine
and resourceful a policeman

42:13.520 --> 42:14.430
as any this force has known.

42:14.560 --> 42:16.597
He will be mourned accordingly.

42:16.720 --> 42:18.518
MAN: Extraordinary.

42:18.640 --> 42:21.996
I need hardly mention how hard this goes
on the morale of our men,

42:22.120 --> 42:25.397
who only so recently lost Inspector Bennet
Drake of the same division.

42:25.520 --> 42:26.510
MAN: Is there any connection between...

42:26.640 --> 42:29.314
How did Inspector Drake
meet his end, though?

42:29.440 --> 42:32.319
- Inspector Shine's last action...
- (CHATTER PAUSES)

42:32.440 --> 42:34.590
...was to secure the arrest
of Edmund Reid,

42:34.720 --> 42:40.238
and whilst...and whilst I know
that man's reputation was hard won,

42:40.360 --> 42:42.351
I hope that you will take
in good faith the charges

42:42.480 --> 42:44.278
which the men of H Division
will soon be presenting

42:44.400 --> 42:46.277
against their one-time station chief.

42:46.400 --> 42:47.310
Charges?

42:47.440 --> 42:48.919
How does this reflect
on the force as a whole, sir?

42:49.040 --> 42:50.360
Let me say only this.

42:50.480 --> 42:52.357
None of the speculation
carried in your pages

42:52.480 --> 42:54.357
is far from the truth of the matter.

42:54.480 --> 42:58.713
And should the courts, as I expect them
to do, find Edmund Reid guilty,

42:58.840 --> 43:01.400
no matter his years of service,

43:01.520 --> 43:05.195
we will be urging for the most severe of
penalties under the law.

43:05.320 --> 43:06.833
(CHATTER)

43:06.960 --> 43:10.032
Commissioner Bradford.
Can this indeed be true?

43:10.160 --> 43:12.151
You would send one of your own
to the rope?

43:18.240 --> 43:19.719
We would, Miss Castello.

43:19.840 --> 43:21.513
With ever greater conviction,

43:21.640 --> 43:22.596
given the vile and headstrong hypocrisy

43:22.720 --> 43:24.950
he has sanctioned
and performed in our name.

43:25.080 --> 43:27.117
(CHATTER)

43:35.000 --> 43:37.913
(CHATTER)

43:40.920 --> 43:43.275
You are Castello?

43:43.400 --> 43:45.596
Good day, Mr Abberline.

43:45.720 --> 43:47.199
Come away, Miss.

43:54.880 --> 43:57.190
- You heard?
- I did.

43:57.320 --> 43:59.550
Then you understand why I wired you.

43:59.680 --> 44:02.069
I hoped you might be prised
from your retirement.

44:02.200 --> 44:04.316
Ed Reid is to be hanged.

44:04.440 --> 44:07.751
That hair-oiled smooth face back there,

44:07.880 --> 44:10.235
that is the Mr Dove you wrote of?

44:10.360 --> 44:12.670
I fear he now has
the wherewithal to prevail.

44:12.800 --> 44:14.791
There are none left to challenge him.

44:14.920 --> 44:16.831
There is you, Miss.

44:16.960 --> 44:20.157
But all I had accumulated of his story,

44:20.280 --> 44:24.274
the murdered Rabbi Ratovski's own
written account, I believe...

44:25.800 --> 44:27.757
...Mr Shine destroyed it.

44:27.880 --> 44:30.679
Then best we put it together again.

44:38.760 --> 44:40.512
Where is Francis Thatcher?

44:41.720 --> 44:44.678
Gone, as you ask. No man knows where.

44:44.800 --> 44:46.552
Not returned?

44:48.000 --> 44:51.038
Mathilda, why does the whereabouts
of Frank Thatcher worry you so?

44:51.160 --> 44:52.992
I'm not sure I want to tell you, Drum.

44:53.120 --> 44:57.796
After all, I know what it is you do with
the secrets I give you.

45:01.040 --> 45:04.192
I would take it back, if I could.

45:06.720 --> 45:07.710
I am sure.

45:07.840 --> 45:09.558
But not for him.

45:09.680 --> 45:12.593
All them things Mr Reid is said
to have done, he done.

45:12.720 --> 45:15.473
- I know. -
So, he must face his punishment.

45:19.960 --> 45:21.792
I understand, Drum.

45:21.920 --> 45:24.434
I did it for you, Tilda.

45:24.560 --> 45:26.437
Because I wanted...

45:26.560 --> 45:31.111
I still only want for you and I to be able
to walk clean of this mess,

45:31.240 --> 45:33.754
for you, for once, to be able to stand
atop the building of your life

45:33.880 --> 45:35.393
and look outward from it,

45:35.520 --> 45:37.352
not forever be casting your gaze
back inside,

45:37.480 --> 45:41.599
for the fear it might catch fire again.

45:42.680 --> 45:44.557
And he is the building, you feel?

45:44.680 --> 45:46.193
Well?

45:47.240 --> 45:48.560
I mean, is he not?

46:09.720 --> 46:10.994
(DOORS BANG)

46:11.120 --> 46:13.839
Yard, son! Pipe down!

46:17.040 --> 46:19.680
Where's your chief?

46:19.800 --> 46:22.519
Mr Abberline.

46:22.640 --> 46:25.154
Mathilda Reid.

46:25.280 --> 46:26.315
Mr Abberline.

46:26.440 --> 46:29.751
On another occasion the men of H Division
would gladly welcome you,

46:29.880 --> 46:33.032
but, as you might have heard, we are
sorely pressed at the present moment.

46:33.160 --> 46:35.356
Who this?

46:35.480 --> 46:37.676
This is Inspector Drummond.

46:37.800 --> 46:38.710
This is him?

46:38.840 --> 46:43.232
The milksop with whom you bring yourself
into shame and disrepute?

46:43.360 --> 46:47.911
Looks like he might battle to blow
the head off a pint of mild.

46:49.080 --> 46:51.117
Nonetheless, sir,

46:51.240 --> 46:53.470
this is my command

46:53.600 --> 46:58.151
and I'd ask you why you've brung yourself
here, today of all days.

47:01.160 --> 47:03.754
(BREATHES HARD)

47:03.880 --> 47:05.791
I would see my friend,

47:05.920 --> 47:10.312
before you and your master have his neck
choked at Newgate.

47:12.760 --> 47:17.789
Tilda, it is not I that will pass
that sentence on him, as you know,

47:17.920 --> 47:19.433
nor Mr Dove.

47:19.560 --> 47:22.313
He agitates for it, however.

47:22.440 --> 47:24.909
Drum, please.

47:25.040 --> 47:26.075
Allow it.

47:27.120 --> 47:29.430
I will not. It is prohibited.

47:31.440 --> 47:33.113
MATHILDA: What is it you do, Drum?

47:33.240 --> 47:36.471
What else? Alert Mr Dove
to this man's presence.

47:36.600 --> 47:40.992
You do it, sonny.
I should be glad to know him.

47:55.200 --> 47:57.032
(DOORS OPEN)

47:57.160 --> 47:59.720
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

47:59.840 --> 48:01.956
(DOORS CREAK SHUT)

48:02.080 --> 48:04.117
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

48:09.880 --> 48:11.393
Hm.

48:15.480 --> 48:17.471
Hello?

48:22.720 --> 48:24.836
Susan?

48:27.000 --> 48:28.354
Captain?

49:10.480 --> 49:11.390
(GASPS)

49:11.520 --> 49:12.999
Who are you?

49:14.600 --> 49:16.876
Wait, wait. Wait.

49:17.000 --> 49:18.434
Aah!

49:18.560 --> 49:20.551
Shut up! Gaah!

49:20.680 --> 49:23.274
- Aaah!
- Be quiet. Be quiet!

49:23.400 --> 49:25.676
Nathaniel! Nathaniel,
you leave her be.

49:45.240 --> 49:47.709
Will you...will you take Connor?

49:47.840 --> 49:50.593
- And leave you here?
- He is a friend.

49:52.400 --> 49:54.391
Trust me.

50:05.720 --> 50:07.438
You brought him here?

50:07.560 --> 50:09.312
Why?

50:15.440 --> 50:17.909
Miss Susan, you told me

50:18.040 --> 50:20.316
and I had to ask him,

50:20.440 --> 50:22.795
because he...he is my brother.

50:24.080 --> 50:26.276
But, Gustus, he swore,

50:26.400 --> 50:28.914
no, he hadn't,

50:29.040 --> 50:31.475
and how could I believe this of him?

50:33.280 --> 50:35.840
But I watched and I followed him...

50:36.880 --> 50:40.760
...and I saw him, he put a
bullet in that copper Thatcher.

50:40.880 --> 50:42.598
LONG SUSAN: Thatcher's dead?

50:42.720 --> 50:43.835
NATHANIEL: Yes.

50:43.960 --> 50:47.635
He put 'em both in the river,
but I swum out and I brought Robin back.

50:50.920 --> 50:52.718
(SIGHS)

50:56.120 --> 50:58.475
Oh, why did you bring him to me?

50:58.600 --> 51:01.035
I've no-one else to go to...

51:02.240 --> 51:04.436
...and I feel as...

51:04.560 --> 51:06.995
as though something should be done

51:07.120 --> 51:12.240
and Robin should be shown
to someone as proof.

51:12.360 --> 51:14.192
Augustus must be punished?

51:17.320 --> 51:18.958
Yeah.

51:20.960 --> 51:23.156
Why?

51:23.280 --> 51:24.634
Because he has killed.

51:24.760 --> 51:26.478
So have you, Nathaniel.

51:26.600 --> 51:28.477
But not a pup.

51:31.840 --> 51:33.513
Never a pup.

51:33.640 --> 51:35.790
Killing is killing...

51:37.120 --> 51:39.031
...and if...

51:41.280 --> 51:43.999
...if Augustus must be
punished...

51:45.040 --> 51:47.190
...then you must.

51:50.800 --> 51:52.791
All who kill...

51:52.920 --> 51:55.309
must be punished.

52:03.600 --> 52:05.591
NATHANIEL: I'm frightened, Miss Susan.

52:05.720 --> 52:07.870
Perhaps...

52:08.000 --> 52:10.389
(SNIFFS)

52:10.520 --> 52:13.239
...perhaps I ought to go with you?

52:21.240 --> 52:22.799
Whoa!

52:31.320 --> 52:33.391
- Thank you.
- Thank you, sir.

52:33.520 --> 52:35.318
Walk on.

52:52.800 --> 52:53.790
Miss Reid.

52:55.640 --> 52:57.517
You did right to send
for me, Inspector.

52:57.640 --> 52:59.597
This him, then, is it?

52:59.720 --> 53:01.996
Mr Abberline.

53:02.120 --> 53:04.077
On another occasion,
I should be grateful to meet you

53:04.200 --> 53:05.599
and account for actions
we here have taken

53:05.720 --> 53:08.792
which I understand must
surely fill you with horror.

53:08.920 --> 53:14.836
But, our force, we comrades cannot be
seen to fight among ourselves.

53:14.960 --> 53:18.157
My, but you are silky and oiled, boy.

53:18.280 --> 53:22.194
However, I'm not in your force no more

53:22.320 --> 53:27.235
and even were I still,
I would not call you my brother-man.

53:27.360 --> 53:29.476
Then, sir, I think Inspector Drummond must
have his men

53:29.600 --> 53:31.557
escort you from these premises.

53:31.680 --> 53:33.353
Mr Drummond.

53:33.480 --> 53:36.199
You men with me.

53:36.320 --> 53:37.469
NATHANIEL: Gustus.

53:52.160 --> 53:53.912
Good afternoon, Mr Dove.

54:00.280 --> 54:03.989
Inspector Drummond,
my name is Caitlin Swift,

54:04.120 --> 54:06.873
and I wish to surrender myself
to the police.

54:07.000 --> 54:08.320
(RAISED VOICES)

54:13.440 --> 54:16.080
My name is Nathaniel Croker...

54:18.240 --> 54:20.800
...and I too wish to surrender myself
to the police.

54:20.920 --> 54:22.911
For what crime?

54:25.320 --> 54:27.470
I'm sorry, Gustus.

54:29.240 --> 54:30.594
I do not know you, sir.

54:33.440 --> 54:35.351
Which crime?

54:40.760 --> 54:41.750
- Murder.
- (PEOPLE TALK)

54:43.200 --> 54:45.271
- DRUMMOND: Whose?
- (RAISED VOICES)

54:48.800 --> 54:50.029
Leon Ratovski.

54:50.160 --> 54:52.595
Rabbi Leon Ratovski.

54:52.720 --> 54:54.472
(RAISED VOICES)

54:55.520 --> 54:58.080
NATHANIEL: Other men,

54:58.200 --> 55:00.760
whose names I did not know...

55:05.640 --> 55:06.789
...and Mr Drake.

55:06.920 --> 55:09.753
(RAISED VOICES)

55:14.120 --> 55:17.238
He known to you, is he, Mr Dove?

55:17.360 --> 55:19.954
He familiar?

55:21.040 --> 55:23.429
I do not know this man.

55:29.760 --> 55:31.671
Get 'em in. Men!

55:33.600 --> 55:36.319
Get them in, all of them! Now!

55:38.920 --> 55:41.036
Mathilda? What is it? What do you do?

55:41.160 --> 55:43.390
Father, I think you must come.

55:45.920 --> 55:47.831
(RAISED VOICES)

55:49.400 --> 55:51.471
just follow procedures, Mr Drummond.

55:51.600 --> 55:54.274
All confessions to be writ,
signed and witnessed.

55:54.400 --> 55:55.993
Yes, sir.

55:56.120 --> 55:59.158
- Renshaw!
- Yes, sir.

55:59.280 --> 56:01.430
You keep away! Right?

56:01.560 --> 56:04.120
- You keep away.
- Nathaniel.

56:04.240 --> 56:05.992
Allow it.

56:06.120 --> 56:08.509
They must see him.

56:32.320 --> 56:35.836
- Who is this boy?
- NATHANIEL: Gustus.

56:35.960 --> 56:37.997
Please.

56:38.120 --> 56:40.680
You know.

56:40.800 --> 56:42.871
Yes, Mr Dove.

56:43.000 --> 56:45.196
- You know.
- (GUN COCKS)

56:45.320 --> 56:48.358
- I'll kill you, you son of a bitch.
- He's not worth the blood.

56:50.520 --> 56:52.238
You taught him...

56:52.360 --> 56:55.034
that he was the beast, did you not?

56:56.040 --> 56:58.839
And that make you more able
to suppress and disguise

56:58.960 --> 57:00.712
your own monstrosity?

57:02.440 --> 57:05.717
Take control of your station house,
Inspector!

57:05.840 --> 57:08.878
Barely have I known you ten minutes, boy,

57:09.000 --> 57:12.994
and already the sound of your voice
makes me want to shit!

57:18.520 --> 57:19.840
Edmund.

57:19.960 --> 57:22.076
REID: Fred.

57:25.600 --> 57:27.159
Samuel Drummond.

57:27.280 --> 57:31.592
You see, your station house has been
overtaken by its prisoners.

57:33.560 --> 57:37.269
You are not to blame.
You were overwhelmed, at gunpoint...

57:42.040 --> 57:45.829
...and your captors then locked down
the station house around you.

58:05.960 --> 58:08.190
(RAISED VOICES)

58:10.160 --> 58:13.949
I knew chaos and horror long before I came
to Whitechapel.

58:15.080 --> 58:16.639
Augustus knew it all.

58:16.760 --> 58:18.831
You're going to leave her be, Drummond.

58:18.960 --> 58:19.472
Caitlin!

58:19.600 --> 58:23.798
ABBERLINE: Think of
what you and I once found.

58:23.920 --> 58:25.638
You are needed here, Mr Reid.

58:25.760 --> 58:28.274
Police. H Division.

